data.Decoration:
Lotus panels surrounding the neck, 
with two floral garlands placed above the points of the lotus panels (middle center of the panels). A dot and circle within the panels at the narrowed top of the panels. Lozenges in a band along the top of the panels. Below the panels (broken off) are what looks like scrolls/swirls.
data.Remarks:
The neck belongs to a yuhuchun vase. 
Yuan dynasty. First of its kind found on Fort Canning hill.
